Name: Allspice Berry Flavor Extract, Organic
Description: What's an allspice berry? An allspice berry is the berry that comes directly from the allspice plant. When dried, it darkens in color and resembles the overall appearance of a peppercorn. The term 'allspice' was actually given to this spice because it was thought to have smelled like literally all the spices. With accents of cinnamon, cloves, and nutmeg, allspice berries are extremely important in Caribbean cuisine. Nature's Flavors Organic Allspice Berry Flavoring is all you need to add great depths of flavor in your recipes to really make them shine. We use real organic fruits and vegetables to create our extracts and we're excited to share this incredible flavor with you.
meta_description: Allspice contains notes of cinnamon, cloves, and nutmeg. At Nature’s Flavors we make it easy to add this Jamaican pepper into your sweet and savory recipes with our Organic Allspice Flavor Extract.

Name: Jamaica Flavor Extract, Organic
Description: Jamaica is commonly known as hibiscus but what makes this extract different from the rest is the lighter hibiscus flavor it provides. Use our Organic Hibiscus Extract, in your teas, jams, ice cream bases, and even smoothies for a light hibiscus taste. At Nature’s Flavors, we believe our extracts are ideal for sodas or other clear drinks since they add a clean flavor without disturbing the color of your beverage. Try using this extract in your favorite sparkling water to give it the true taste of jamaica! Just add 2 to 4 drops of extract to every 8 ounces of the liquid and stir well. This extract is 100% organic, meaning the ingredients we use in our extracts are certified organic. Always plant-based ingredients and never any added chemicals. Name: Raspberry Flavor Extract, Organic - TTB Approved
Description: If you enjoy the fresh taste of ripened red raspberries, then you’re in for a real treat. Our TTB approved flavors are ideal for any of your alcoholic beverage making needs as well as usage with tobacco. Since our flavor extracts are concentrated, a little will go a long way. It’s best for experiment with using our flavor extracts by using a little bit and then increase dosage if needed. Since each application or recipe is different and is compiled of unique ingredients, there is no set ratio as to how much should be used. A good rule of thumb, however, is to use anywhere from .25% - 4% flavoring of your total ingredients. This is, though, a general guide, so it is possible to need to use less or more depending upon varying factors. Since this product is organic certified, we assure that you will receive the best product possible for your TTB approved creations. Beer, wine, liquor, cigarettes, cigars, and more can all benefit from the great taste of Organic Raspberry Flavor Extract. If you’ve wanted to create a great raspberry flavored beer or perhaps a raspberry flavor infused vodka, then this just may be exactly what you need.

Name: Strawberry Flavor Extract, Organic
Description: Organic Strawberry Extract is a natural flavor extract that contains the great taste of freshly picked strawberries. Excellent for baking, ice cream, coffee syrups and beverage applications, this extract is certain to add a great and fruity taste to your many recipes. It can be used in a plentitude of creative ways. And, since our flavor extracts are concentrated, a little will go a long way. We urge you to experiment with your flavors when you are first trying them out. Because recipes are not all the same, different quantities will be needed to reach desired effects. As a starting point, you may begin with as little as .25% of your total ingredients, but may find yourself using up to 4%. Begin with using a smaller amount, and then slowly add more if you find you need to. Some level of experimentation will be necessary to find the ratios that are right for your and your unique application.

Name: Sweet Corn Flavor Extract, Organic
Description: Our flavor extracts are ideal for baking as well as for flavoring clear liquids like beverages, beer, wine, and alcohols. They are high heat stable as well as water soluble. Our flavor extracts are not sweetened, so we suggest adding a sweetener of your own or use an acid along with the product to make the flavors naturally pop. When first using one of our flavor extracts, especially for the first time, we suggest that you do a little experimenting. Since each application and each recipe varies from one to the next, there is never a one-size-fits-all approach to a typical flavor dosage. Variables include recipe size, recipe ingredients, temperature the recipe will be cooked at (if any length at all), and essentially what you are trying to make in the first place. Nature’s Flavors Organic Sweet Corn Flavor Extract contains all the enjoyment of a farm fresh ear of corn--bright, succulent, fresh. Try using this in baked goods like cakes, cupcakes, and more. With this radiant flavor, you’ll find the possibilities are limitless and you’ll have fun experimenting, too.

Name: Organic Allspice Flavor Extract Without Diacetyl
Description: The processes for making organic flavors are much the same as for making natural flavors. The ingredients are organic rather than just natural. You start by using only certified organic ingredients when available and when not you may use naturals provided they fit with in the definition of natural and only comprise less than 5% of the total amount when calling it 95% organic. When calling it 100% organic you must use only certified organic ingredients and nothing else. Nature's Flavours carries both 95% and 100% certified organic flavors. It is our goal to produce only 100% organic flavor concentrates and extracts as the ingredients become available. In many instances we produce our own organic ingredients to satisfy our strict quality control requirements. Because the industry is still very young the technology's to make these ingredients are still evolving. The only solvents that we use in the development of organic and natural flavors are filtered RO water and organic alcohol. If we can't extract the ingredients through these methods then we don't do it. Steam distillation is another method we employee. Fortunately this is in most cases the only methods needed to manufacture these unique flavor concentrates and extracts. A simple and common process for making vanilla extract is to take organic vanilla beans and grind them to a pulp then allow them to soak and extract in an organic alcohol/water mixture for a period of time sometimes for up to several months. Normally for a standard organic vanilla extract you would extract for a period of not less than fourteen days. That's how long Nature's Flavours allows its organic vanilla extract to age and extract. This method is common for our citrus and other fruit flavor extracts as well. There are usually some filtering and clarifying techniques that follow the extraction process before being bottled or packaged. There are no chemical residues because there are no chemical solvents used. Many of the organic flavoring ingredients are derived this way first before being incorporated in to water based or oil based organic flavor concentrate. To make the organic flavor concentrates water soluble you must emulsify the oils that were derived and separated from the extraction process or steam distilling and that usually involves using an organic gum or starch and under high pressure and shearing. This process forces the oils and Gums to be broken into very small particles and cling to one another with out reforming into there basic building blocks again. The entire process is safe and effective for producing the finest organic flavor oils, flavor concentrates, and flavor extracts. Nature's Flavours has pioneered many of these methods for producing these organic products. We are proud of our flavorings, spices, coffees, and all our organic products. We hope they bring you much enjoyment and satisfaction.

Name: Organic Citrus Flavor Extract Without Diacetyl
Description: ou start by using only certified organic ingredients when available and when not you may use naturals provided they fit with in the definition of natural and only comprise less than 5% of the total amount when calling it 95% organic. When calling it 100% organic you must use only certified organic ingredients and nothing else. Natures Flavours carries both 95% and 100% certified organic flavors. It is our goal to produce only 100% organic flavor concentrates and extracts as the ingredients become available. In many instances we produce our own organic ingredients to satisfy our strict quality control requirements. Because the industry is still very young the technology's to make these ingredients are still evolving. The only solvents that we use in the development of organic and natural flavors are filtered RO water and organic alcohol. If we can't extract the ingredients thru these methods then we don't do it. Steam distillation is another method we employee. Fortunately this is in most cases the only methods needed to manufacture these unique flavor concentrates and extracts. A simple and common process for making vanilla extract is to take organic vanilla beans and grind them to a pulp then allow them to soak and extract in an organic alcohol/water mixture for a period of time sometimes for up to several months. Normally for a standard organic vanilla extract you would extract for a period of not less than fourteen days. That's how long Natures Flavours allows its organic vanilla extract to age and extract. This method is common for our citrus and other fruit flavor extracts as well. There are usually some filtering and clarifying techniques that follow the extraction process before being bottled or packaged. There are no chemical residues because there are no chemical solvents used. Many of the organic flavoring ingredients are derived this way first before being incorporated in to water based or oil based organic flavor concentrate. To make the organic flavor concentrates water soluble you must emulsify the oils that were derived and separated from the extraction process or steam distilling and that usually involves using an organic gum or starch and under high pressure and shearing. This process forces the oils and gums to be broken into very small particles and cling to one another with out reforming into there basic building blocks again. The entire process is safe and effective for producing the finest organic flavor oils, flavor concentrates, and flavor extracts. Natures Flavours has pioneered many of these methods for producing these organic products. We are proud of our flavorings, spices, coffees, and all our organic products. We hope they bring you much enjoyment and satisfaction.

Name: Organic Elderflower Flavor Extract Without Diacetyl
Description: The processes for making organic flavors are much the same as for making natural flavors. The ingredients are organic rather than just natural. You start by using only certified organic ingredients when available and when not you may use naturals provided they fit with in the definition of natural and only comprise less than 5% of the total amount when calling it 95% organic. When calling it 100% organic you must use only certified organic ingredients and nothing else. Nature's Flavours carries both 95% and 100% certified organic flavors. It is our goal to produce only 100% organic flavor concentrates and extracts as the ingredients become available. In many instances we produce our own organic ingredients to satisfy our strict quality control requirements. Because the industry is still very young the technology's to make these ingredients are still evolving. The only solvents that we use in the development of organic and natural flavors are filtered RO water and organic alcohol. If we can't extract the ingredients through these methods then we don't do it. Steam distillation is another method we employee. Fortunately this is in most cases the only methods needed to manufacture these unique flavor concentrates and extracts. A simple and common process for making vanilla extract is to take organic vanilla beans and grind them to a pulp then allow them to soak and extract in an organic alcohol/water mixture for a period of time sometimes for up to several months. Normally for a standard organic vanilla extract you would extract for a period of not less than fourteen days. That's how long Nature's Flavours allows its organic vanilla extract to age and extract. This method is common for our citrus and other fruit flavor extracts as well. There are usually some filtering and clarifying techniques that follow the extraction process before being bottled or packaged. There are no chemical residues because there are no chemical solvents used. Many of the organic flavoring ingredients are derived this way first before being incorporated in to water based or oil based organic flavor concentrate. To make the organic flavor concentrates water soluble you must emulsify the oils that were derived and separated from the extraction process or steam distilling and that usually involves using an organic gum or starch and under high pressure and shearing. This process forces the oils and Gums to be broken into very small particles and cling to one another with out reforming into there basic building blocks again. The entire process is safe and effective for producing the finest organic flavor oils, flavor concentrates, and flavor extracts. Nature's Flavours has pioneered many of these methods for producing these organic products. We are proud of our flavorings, spices, coffees, and all our organic products. We hope they bring you much enjoyment and satisfaction.

Name: Organic Jalapeno Flavor Extract Without Diacetyl
Description: You start by using only certified organic ingredients when available and when not you may use naturals provided they fit with in the definition of natural and only comprise less than 5% of the total amount when calling it 95% organic. When calling it 100% organic you must use only certified organic ingredients and nothing else. Nature's Flavours carries both 95% and 100% certified organic flavors. It is our goal to produce only 100% organic flavor concentrates and extracts as the ingredients become available. In many instances we produce our own organic ingredients to satisfy our strict quality control requirements. Because the industry is still very young the technology's to make these ingredients are still evolving. The only solvents that we use in the development of organic and natural flavors are filtered RO water and organic alcohol. If we can't extract the ingredients through these methods then we don't do it. Steam distillation is another method we employee. Fortunately this is in most cases the only methods needed to manufacture these unique flavor concentrates and extracts. A simple and common process for making vanilla extract is to take organic vanilla beans and grind them to a pulp then allow them to soak and extract in an organic alcohol/water mixture for a period of time sometimes for up to several months. Normally for a standard organic vanilla extract you would extract for a period of not less than fourteen days. That's how long Nature's Flavours allows its organic vanilla extract to age and extract. This method is common for our citrus and other fruit flavor extracts as well. There are usually some filtering and clarifying techniques that follow the extraction process before being bottled or packaged. There are no chemical residues because there are no chemical solvents used. Many of the organic flavoring ingredients are derived this way first before being incorporated in to water based or oil based organic flavor concentrate. To make the organic flavor concentrates water soluble you must emulsify the oils that were derived and separated from the extraction process or steam distilling and that usually involves using an organic gum or starch and under high pressure and shearing. This process forces the oils and Gums to be broken into very small particles and cling to one another with out reforming into there basic building blocks again. The entire process is safe and effective for producing the finest organic flavor oils, flavor concentrates, and flavor extracts. Nature's Flavours has pioneered many of these methods for producing these organic products. We are proud of our flavorings, spices, coffees, and all our organic products. We hope they bring you much enjoyment and satisfaction.

Name: Organic Merlot Flavor Extract Without Diacetyl
Description: The processes for making organic flavors are much the same as for making natural flavors. The ingredients are organic rather than just natural. You start by using only certified organic ingredients when available and when not you may use naturals provided they fit with in the definition of natural and only comprise less than 5% of the total amount when calling it 95% organic. When calling it 100% organic you must use only certified organic ingredients and nothing else. Nature's Flavours carries both 95% and 100% certified organic flavors. It is our goal to produce only 100% organic flavor concentrates and extracts as the ingredients become available. In many instances we produce our own organic ingredients to satisfy our strict quality control requirements. Because the industry is still very young the technology's to make these ingredients are still evolving. The only solvents that we use in the development of organic and natural flavors are filtered RO water and organic alcohol. If we can't extract the ingredients through these methods then we don't do it. Steam distillation is another method we employee. Fortunately this is in most cases the only methods needed to manufacture these unique flavor concentrates and extracts. A simple and common process for making vanilla extract is to take organic vanilla beans and grind them to a pulp then allow them to soak and extract in an organic alcohol/water mixture for a period of time sometimes for up to several months. Normally for a standard organic vanilla extract you would extract for a period of not less than fourteen days. That's how long Nature's Flavours allows its organic vanilla extract to age and extract. This method is common for our citrus and other fruit flavor extracts as well. There are usually some filtering and clarifying techniques that follow the extraction process before being bottled or packaged. There are no chemical residues because there are no chemical solvents used. Many of the organic flavoring ingredients are derived this way first before being incorporated in to water based or oil based organic flavor concentrate. To make the organic flavor concentrates water soluble you must emulsify the oils that were derived and separated from the extraction process or steam distilling and that usually involves using an organic gum or starch and under high pressure and shearing. This process forces the oils and Gums to be broken into very small particles and cling to one another with out reforming into there basic building blocks again. The entire process is safe and effective for producing the finest organic flavor oils, flavor concentrates, and flavor extracts. Nature's Flavours has pioneered many of these methods for producing these organic products. We are proud of our flavorings, spices, coffees, and all our organic products. We hope they bring you much enjoyment and satisfaction.

Name: Dragon Fruit Flavor Concentrate, Organic
Description:
Dragon fruit is one of the most mysterious flavors. As The Flavor Guy, I have gone through great lengths to study this fruit. Recently, I ventured to Cambodia and Vietnam to study the dragon fruit. In many parts of the world, it is also called pitaya. What I discovered is that it comes in many various colors in different countries. It is served in many restaurants, especially as a breakfast fruit or in smoothies.

As a flavor chemist, I'm always looking for the most unique flavors I can bring back to the United States and introduce them to customers. In 2014, on a trip to Cambodia, I discovered the magenta hued dragon fruit and experienced its very pleasant flavor. It was so different from the white fleshed fruit, which I first tasted 20 years earlier on a trip to Guanzhou, China. The dragon fruit with the white flesh has little to no flavor at all and is really more about texture and its unusual white and speckled center.

The colorful dragon fruits are very flavorful and a real treat. Chemical analysis on both GC/MS and HPLC reveals that white fleshed dragon fruit has a lot less going on than the red, purple, or magenta colored varieties. At the time of writing this article, I'm in Kauai, Hawaii checking out the dragon fruit that grows here. It seems that the whole world is discovering this unique flavor.

The flavor of the red dragon fruit is amazing it is sweet with a slight acidic background. It has a subtle berry flavor. Analysis of the flavor reveals a very high ester count with a range similar to grapes and berries. More about the flavor components later.

This dragon fruit flavor is designed for use in baking, dairy, beverages, and any application where a water-soluble flavor with a high-heat tenacity is needed.

Name: Acorn Flavor Concentrate, Organic
Description:
First off, you might be thinking, 'Acorn Flavor Concentrate?' And while you have every right to question this unique flavor, it's got some really delicious culinary possibilities. In the past, most of us have left acorns to the squirrels, but the next time you come across a supply of these funny little nuts, think again. Acorns can be ground into acorn meal or acorn flour to make acorn pancakes, acorn tamales, or even acorn cake. Additionally, acorns can be pickled, creamed into an acorn butter, added to an acorn stew, or roasted to create acorn coffee or acorn brittle candy. There's a world of acorn flavor to explore and Nature's Flavors can help you open that door. Sure, it may sound a little nutty, but make sure to add our Organic Acorn Flavor Concentrate to your online cart--you never know what you'll come up with. Use our organic concentrates for baking recipes, dairy applications like ice cream and yogurt, smoothies, and more. And, since our line of organic concentrates are made from some of the purest ingredients that Mother Earth has to offer, there's never a reason to worry about what's in the bottle. Just real honest to goodness ingredients, so you can make real honest to goodness recipes. Don't let those squirrels pack their cheeks full of acorns this fall. Pack your cheeks with this awesome nutty acorn flavor instead.

Name: Anise Flavor Concentrate, Organic
Description:
Nature's Flavors Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate is made from 100% organic anise seed. The organic anise seeds are extracted through steam distillation and the essential oil is collected and saved for further processing. Nature's Flavors Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate is made to be water soluble by homogenization with gum acacia and the fresh steam distilled anise oil. The flavor of anise resembles licorice and fennel, but with a slightly sweeter note. Nature's Flavors Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate can be used to flavor ice cream, beverages, sauces, syrups, liquors, cakes, cookies, yogurts, and other dairy products. Additionally, it can be used in cleaning solutions as well. Like many essential oil-based products, anise has powerful anti-microbial properties. Add Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate and to a bucket of water and clean floors and counter tops. It is heat stable and can be baked in cake recipes or cookies to 375 degrees for up to one hour. Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate can also be pasteurized in dairy products and is stable in UHT sytems. Because anise is a sweet flavor, it is easy to over-flavor. Care should be taken to not over-flavor any product. Signs of over-flavoring include a taste on the palate or a minty feeling. When using Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate, you should only be able to taste the finished product for about 3 to 5 seconds after you swallow the product. If you taste it for longer than 3-5 seconds, then you have used too much.

Ingredients: Water, Organic Gum Acacia, Organic extracts of anise seed

Name: Berry Flavor Concentrate, Organic
Description:
By using Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate in your food preparations, you can have that summertime feel in your cooking year-round. Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate has a fresh and fruity taste that will bring that little splash of sunshine to the dullest of meals. Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate can be used to create spectacular meals that will make you feel like you are lounging by a pool on a warm summer day. Even living in a warm climate, there are times throughout the year that berries just aren't in season. Having the Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate on-hand to use in smoothies, beverages, and all types of cooking and baking is just like having fresh berries in your kitchen. You will never have to worry about spoilage or wasting unused fruit, as the Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate can be used in any season. Some examples of berries are blueberries, cranberries, currants, elderberries, gooseberries, and grapes. Berry is used to describe a small edible fruit that is usually quite juicy. Berries can be round or oblong and bright in color and can be sweet or sour. Organic Berry Concentrate has hints of berry taste with a sweet and tangy flavor. Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate can be used in all types of baking and cooking. Use it in breads, cakes, and cookies. These baked goods are a nice treat and are a great way to spread a little sunshine in the lives of your family and friends. Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate can also be used in sauces, icings, and beverages. When creating meals and drinks with Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate, you will create memories with your family that will last a lifetime. Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate would be especially good in dessert making. Just imagine adding it to your favorite cheesecake or cake recipes. By using Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate, it's like having the taste of berries without having to have fresh berries on-hand. Organic Berry Flavored Concentrate has the fresh, summer-like taste of sweet berries. Berries have been known to have wonderful health benefits. Berries are a great source of Vitamin C that you need to boost the immune system. The also are a good source of magnesium and potassium. Berries are low in calories and promote a good healthy diet.

Name: Chestnut Flavor Concentrate, Organic
Description:
Nature's Flavors Organic Chestnut Flavor Concentrate is 100% organic. The essential oils are emulsified and stabilized into a water soluble form. This organic chestnut flavor can be used in baking. It is heat stable up to 375 degrees, up to one hour. It works well in dairy applications, such as puddings, milkshakes, and protein shakes. In addition, organic chestnut flavor is a great way to make your baked goods, such as pies, cookies, cakes, and breads, a delicious delight! Nature's Flavors Organic Chestnut Flavor is very strong, so a little goes a long way. Care should be taken to not use too much or over-flavor a product. If you taste the flavor longer than 3 to 5 seconds on your palate, or if you're tasting a metallic, or taste than you have over-flavored the product. Remember, more is not always better. Just enough to tease the taste buds. But don't try to satisfy yourself or your customer with a lot of flavor. Blending our Organic Vanilla Extract or our Vanilla Flavor Concentrate with the Organic Chestnut Flavor Concentrate will further smooth and blend the flavor. Vanilla extracts act as an enhancer much the same way as cream and sugar are to coffee.

Name: Maple Flavor Concentrate, Organic
Description:
Nature's Flavors' Organic Maple Flavor Concentrate contains the notes of 100% Organic Maple Syrup. Perfect for your baking needs and beverages, the Organic Maple Flavor Concentrate is high heat stable, water based, and contains no sweeteners. Here, we list a couple ideas to help you use this Organic Maple Flavor Concentrate, but the uses are endless. To make your own organic maple flavored syrup, start with 8 ounces of distilled or purified water in a sauce pan and heat on low heat. To this, add a quarter cup of organic cane sugar and 2 ounces of Organic Powdered Dextrose. You may substitute the Organic Dextrose with Organic Tapioca Syrup. Add this to warm water and stir until completely dissolved. Bring the temperature up to 195 degrees F. Cool and add 1/4 teaspoon of Organic Maple Flavor Concentrate. Stir to dissolve. You can use it immediately or store in the refrigerator until needed. To make a sugar-free maple flavored syrup, start with 8 ounces of water in a sauce pan and heat on low. In a separate bowl, combine 2 dry ounces of our SweetenFX Sugar Free Sweetener and Carrageenan gum then add to the warm water and bring up the temperature slowly to 195 degrees F. Now, add 1/4 teaspoon of Organic Maple Flavor Concentrate and cool the mixture. Refrigerate unused syrup.

Ingredients: Water, Organic Gum Acacia, Organ%ic Flavors.

Name: Sweet Corn Flavor Concentrate, Organic
Description:
What is Organic Sweet Corn Flavor Concentrate? Nature's Flavors Organic Sweet Corn Flavor Concentrate has all the summertime freshness of ripe corn in a convenient form of a flavor concentrate. Great for baked goods, dairy products, and beverages, add great corn flavor to just about any recipe you’d like. Perhaps add extra rich corn flavor to cornbread, to cereals, or even whip up a great sweet corn flavored ice cream or frozen yogurt. Nature’s Flavors invites you to experiment with our flavor concentrates. Since there are no one-size-fits-all ratios for how much to use, we suggest that you begin with using a little, and then gradually increase your dosage upon your personal preference. Try Organic Sweet Corn Flavor Concentrate alone with recipe ingredients or try mixing two or more organic flavor concentrates to achieve a more layered, complex taste. Nature’s Flavors is proud to use the best organic ingredients in order to craft our organic flavor concentrates. This product is high-heat stable, water based, and unsweetened.

Name: Organic Almond Cream Flavor Concentrate Without Diacetyl
Description: Nature's Flavors Organic almond cream flavor concentrate is 100% organic. The essential oils are emulsified and stabilized into a water soluble form. Nature's Flavors organic almond cream flavor can be used in many recipes. This organic almond cream flavor can be used in baking since the almond cream is heat stable up to 375 degrees and up to one hour. This organic almond cream flavor will work well in dairy applications such as ice cream and yogurt as well as milk shakes and protein drinks. In addition, the organic almond cream flavor will be excellent for pies, cakes, cookies and other sweet desserts. Nature's Flavors organic almond cream flavor concentrate is very strong and a little goes a long way. Care should be taken to not use too much or over flavor a product. If you taste the flavor longer than 3 to 5 seconds on your palate or if you are tasting a metallic or taste, then you have over flavored the product, which will cause you to burp almond cola for an hour following ingestion. Remember, more is not always better. Use just enough to tease the taste buds, but dont try to satisfy yourself or your customer with a lot of flavor. Over flavoring usually means you will become tired of the flavor quickly and never use it again. Blending our organic extract or flavor concentrate with the organic almond cola flavor concentrate will smooth out the flavor and enhance it, causing you to use less flavor while smoothing out any rough edges in the taste. extracts act like an enhancer much the same way as cream and sugar are to coffee.

Description: Our Nature's Flavors Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate is made to be water soluble by homogenization with Gum Acacia and the fresh steam distilled anise oil. The flavor of anise resembles licorice and fennel, but with a slightly sweeter note. Nature's Flavors Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate can be used to flavor ice creams, beverages, sauces, syrups, liquors, cakes, cookies, preparations, cleaning solutions, yogurts, and other dairy products. Like many essential oil-based products, anise has powerful anti-microbial properties. You can take the Organic Anise Flavor Concentrate and add it to a bucket of water and clean floors and counter tops, even! It is heat stable and can be baked in cake recipes or cookies to 375 degrees for up to one hour. This Anise Flavor can also be pasteurized in dairy products and is stable in UHT sytems. Because Anise is a sweet flavor, it is easy to over-flavor. Care should be taken to not over-flavor any product. Signs of over-flavoring include a taste on the palate, or a minty feeling. When using Anise Flavor you should only be able to taste the finished product for about 3 to 5 seconds after you swallow the product. If you taste the Anise Flavor longer than 3 to 5 seconds than you have used too much. Ingredients: Water, Organic Gum Acacia, Organic extracts of anise seed.
